The seduction game you play is tried, true, and still effective: hard to get. You know that the best seducers turn the tables - and get their crush to seduce them. My Grams picked up a $2 scratchers ticket this morning. It was one of those Crossword puzzle ones. Well i get a phone call around 10 this morning from my mother saying that grams won $500. I was like wow. Well I get home and I want to go rent Vanity Fair from Hollywood Video. So we go. And then on the way back we stop at FRY's to try to cash in the ticket. Grams had tried at BASHA's earlier in the day but they could only do $100 or less. We get to the costomer service counter and the woman runs the ticket through the scanner. "Hey, lady," says the woman,"You musta won biiiiigggg. I can't cash this." 
We inform her that we won $500. 
"Noooo. It hasta be more than that. We can cash up to $500. You won big." 
We tell her that there was only 8 words and that means $500. So we count up the words. There was only 8. "Must be a mistake then" the woman suggested. 
We thanked her and left. We get in the truck and I realize something. I tell grams to let me see the ticket. Se gives it to me. I look it over and then I realize that we were wrong. 
"Its nine. There are nine words." 
"What?" grams looked at me like I was nuts. 
"Ummm, well, you forgot to scratch of a C. See?" 
"Oh. Well how much is nine words?"
"Ahhhhhhhhh. Oh my." I was speechless for a second.
"Tanya, how much is-"
"Twentyfivehundreddollars." I said in a rush.
"Oh my...my...my."

Now if only I could win a boyfriend.

I can't make up my mind. I was going to audition for Director's Training Group but then I decided I just didn't have the patience for it. Maybe it was a tiddle bit of the fact that I know I wouldn't get in so why bring my self pain? BUT for a week I have decided that I will audition for DTG then the next day I won't. Now I have decided. I have decided that I am going to ask MB if I can still have audition material for Writer's Circle BECAUSE I have no chance for DTG. I think I would have a better chance with WC even though I personally always think my writing sucks. But then again that could be due to the fact that I always write stuff the day before it is due so it isn't any good. I swear I won't do that for WC.

Of course MB wouldn't admit that to just anyone. That little girl was just lucky that I didn't throw a book at her head instead. That rhymed. Anyway Next time she is singing I just might kick her out of the black box OR maybe I will just tell her that if she has any hope at all of getting a part in the musical she would be wise to shut it before MB really begins to hate her.>

Anyway I've got to go to Sonic now. Adios Amigos.

I love baking. I made 72 cupcakes. That's right. 72. And the frosting colors are: Blue, Green, Red, Yellow and Purple. Plus sprinkles. I had fun tonight. Baking relaxes me for some reason. I don't know why...
And I didn't make it. Maybe I wouldn't feel so terrible if I wasn't the only one who didn't make that was in Ensemble last year...

So...today was... very nerve-wracking. Last callbacks. A lot of very talented people. I was nervous before but now that it is done, I'm not. Maybe because I know it is done and what's done is done and can't be changed. I hope that I get to be in Ensemble again. It would be a miracle if I do. I think my auditions went well, but I also think that everyone else's went excellent. I don't know. I just don't have much faith in myself. But regardless if I make it in or not, I will still be happy for those that do and sad for those that don't. It is a very sought after position.

I finished my college application essay. Woo-hoo. It only took me and hour and a half and I think it rocks. I'm sure Mr. Black will find many things wrong with it. Oh well. I'll fix it.

I discovered while visiting POGB today that I have a 116% in one of my classes. It must be a mistake. I'll have to talk to my teacher.

All my other classes are going very well and that makes me very happy. Well, I need to go work on even more homework. And eat my Brownie earthquake from Dairy Queen.

Ensemble auditions are going good. So far. 

Monday for the first auditions there was about 60 people who showed up. Most of us didn't get out of there until 6 o'clock. It took for-EVER. I personally did horrible on those. I waited too long and I had racked up my nerves so...yeah. I don't like to think about it. I saw alot of people practicing in the hall that I thought were pretty good. And most of them made it.

Tuesday, today, First Callbacks. 25 left. A lot better for me I think. Not my best...most everyone else did really well though. I thought Sam Jensen did a great Tina. Slap the BITCH. That's right. There was slappage. Kelsey Tortsvite did an excellent Tina too. She made ME cry! Jeez. All in all there was alot of good people. A LOT of females there. Only 6 guys.

I don't think I am going to get in this time. I thought last year was some sort of mistake or that Mr. Bush lost his marbles temporarily. Like I said. A lot of talent there. Only one freshman. I can't remember her name...

Tomorrow, Second Callbacks. I think it is only going to be 15 people. Not sure who. It's a surprise. Then he will cut it down to 9 or 10 for the Final List. There were 7 people who auditioned that were in Ensemble last year. That leaves 2 or 3 open spots IF everyone makes it in again.

I guess we will find out soon enough...

Tomorrow. Another installment of...THE AUDITION.

You called me names, you made me cry,
You made me wish that I could die.
Your taunts were pains i'll never tell,
I hope you burn and die in hell.
Maybe that was a bit too strong,
I could never hold a grudge that long.
But my amnity is lost towards you,
Of this, at least, I know is true.
I'll never try to be your friend,
And if you try I'll put an end
To all your folly and all your pride.
So you, in truth, should step aside.
'Cause you dont know me but I know you,
There are many out there just like you.
You're nothing but another clone,
Society-altered but Godly-sown.
So in you I know there's good,
Though not as much as I think you should.
But still I thank you for your hate,
After all, it was a part of fate.
From hate a fiery passion was born,
And now your taunts go on forlorn.
For I am, already, on fire.
So great a blaze not to admire.
So bright a light not to hide away.
So strong a will not to obey.
So torrid a flame not to retreat.
So abundant a fuel not to depleat.
So feed the fire, and watch it grow,
Force the urge back down below.
With a bucket drain a moat,
Send the curses back down your throat.
Learn a lesson, heed it well,
Take pride in that you'll never tell.

Hey!

I hope this gets to all of you.  I know I have correct e-mail addresses for some of you but the others may get bounced back.  So, if you have the correct e-mail addresses for Ben, Skylar, Jessica, Jake, Preston or Emily, please forward it to them.

Anyway....

I got word, yesterday, that VOICES AND OTHER DISTURBANCES was selected for a workshop/showcase production by a theatre company in New York.  According to the company's Artiistic Director, the group's Executive Producer of the company has "called dibs" on directing the play herself.   I restructured the play to be performed by 5 actors (3 female/2 male) for their production.  No dialogue has changed.   One of the cool things about the restructuring, is that I changed Actor 1, Actor 2, et. al. in the opening sequence to use your actual names.  So the play now has characters named for all the 2004-2005 NCTE members.

Here's the summary/teaser that accompanied the script that they read to consider it for production:

Ballpark franks and a boss not washing his hands after using the restroom.  A pop star whose sanity is slipping away.  Whose thoughts merely meander through a few trivial twists and turns and whose mind is truly twisted?  VOICES AND OTHER DISTURBANCES explores the lives of a quirky assortment of characters. The approach is irreverent and amusing and audiences will ponder dryer lint, a cheerleader with a broken neck and whether or not to order the flounder and call their mother.

Do you hear voices?  Use Lemon Pledge.

I will most likely go back to New York to see the production.  But, of course, I've already seen the original cast.  :)

My best,
mb
